{"nodes": [{"id": "docs_api_scale_readiness_100k_users_scale_readiness_review", "label": "API Scale Readiness Review (100k Users)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "docs/api-scale-readiness-100k-users.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Verdict: 100k registered users is plausible after index/query cleanup; 100k concurrent users is not, given a single Node process, 20-connection DB pool, and SQL-heavy live endpoints. All fixes deliberately preserve the frontend API contract."}, {"id": "docs_api_scale_readiness_100k_users_unbounded_admin_queries", "label": "Unbounded Admin Queries", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/api-scale-readiness-100k-users.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Admin endpoints (getallusers, getpayoutlogs, getallpartner, etc. in AdminDbController.js) return full tables with no pagination, causing memory blowup and table scans at scale. Fix: default server-side pagination with capped limits while keeping response shape."}, {"id": "docs_api_scale_readiness_100k_users_runtime_db_sync", "label": "Runtime DB Sync In Production", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/api-scale-readiness-100k-users.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Production boot runs connection.sync({force:false}) in src/core/database/initialize.js \u2014 schema changes at runtime, startup races between instances, unversioned schema. Recommended fix: versioned migrations run as a deploy step."}, {"id": "docs_api_scale_readiness_100k_users_index_strategy", "label": "Database Index Strategy", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/api-scale-readiness-100k-users.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Recommends composite indexes on User, UserSession, Store, StoreSession, appointments, appointment_items, Reviews, Favourites, PartnerAddress, StoreServices, WalletLogs, NotificationLogs \u2014 the highest-leverage scale fix requiring no API change."}, {"id": "docs_api_scale_readiness_100k_users_notification_queueing", "label": "Notification Queueing (Background Workers)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/api-scale-readiness-100k-users.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "FirebaseService.notifyOrderStatus sends FCM multicast directly in request paths and admin flows load all device tokens into memory. Fix: queue jobs (BullMQ+Redis or similar) so the API returns fast and workers batch sends."}, {"id": "docs_api_scale_readiness_100k_users_idempotent_payment_finalization", "label": "Idempotent Payment Finalization", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/api-scale-readiness-100k-users.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Duplicate paymentsucssess calls can double-apply wallet/notification side effects; payment update must check existing status/payment id and run in a transaction. Critical-priority fix."}, {"id": "docs_api_scale_readiness_100k_users_redis_rate_limiting", "label": "Redis-Backed Rate Limiting", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/api-scale-readiness-100k-users.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Current rate limits on OTP routes are in-memory, so they break across multiple app instances. Redis-backed limits needed on OTP, login, payment, search, report, and upload endpoints before horizontal scaling."}, {"id": "docs_api_scale_readiness_100k_users_observability", "label": "Observability (Metrics, Logs, APM)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/api-scale-readiness-100k-users.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Recommends request ids, structured JSON logs, latency/error/pool metrics, and APM; notes the /status endpoint only returns a static response and pool stats are noisily console-logged every 5 seconds."}], "edges": [{"source": "docs_api_scale_readiness_100k_users_notification_queueing", "target": "docs_admin_targeted_notification_api_broadcast_notification", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "INFERRED", "confidence_score": 0.85, "source_file": "docs/api-scale-readiness-100k-users.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_api_scale_readiness_100k_users_scale_readiness_review", "target": "docs_api_scale_readiness_100k_users_unbounded_admin_queries", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/api-scale-readiness-100k-users.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_api_scale_readiness_100k_users_scale_readiness_review", "target": "docs_api_scale_readiness_100k_users_runtime_db_sync", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/api-scale-readiness-100k-users.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_api_scale_readiness_100k_users_scale_readiness_review", "target": "docs_api_scale_readiness_100k_users_index_strategy", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/api-scale-readiness-100k-users.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_api_scale_readiness_100k_users_scale_readiness_review", "target": "docs_api_scale_readiness_100k_users_notification_queueing", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/api-scale-readiness-100k-users.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_api_scale_readiness_100k_users_scale_readiness_review", 